00:17:24.920 --> 00:17:27.359
Next question, do you have tips on

00:17:27.359 --> 00:17:29.160
ways to politely educate colleagues?

00:17:31.160 --> 00:17:32.920
On the importance of

00:17:32.920 --> 00:17:35.119
formatting to record data?

00:17:35.119 --> 00:17:37.219
Well, didn't you see the sad face in my

00:17:37.219 --> 00:17:37.920
blog post?

00:17:37.920 --> 00:17:40.219
It said, please don't do this, sad face.

00:17:40.219 --> 00:17:43.619
No, so it's I think the

00:17:43.619 --> 00:17:46.119
what seems to work is just empathy and

00:17:46.119 --> 00:17:48.619
being nice rather than being snarky.

00:17:48.619 --> 00:17:51.020
And maybe like identifying good

00:17:51.020 --> 00:17:52.819
resources like the paper I showed and

00:17:52.819 --> 00:17:55.920
just maybe print them out and leave them

00:17:55.920 --> 00:17:57.520
leave them somewhere.

00:17:57.520 --> 00:17:58.319
I don't know.

00:17:58.319 --> 00:18:00.319
It's what I've tried in my own work

00:18:00.319 --> 00:18:02.020
environments and it seems to be working.

00:18:02.020 --> 00:18:04.619
Just certainly scatter them on their desks.

00:18:04.619 --> 00:18:05.119
Yeah.

00:18:08.020 --> 00:18:10.020
All right, thank you, Luis.

00:18:10.020 --> 00:18:11.219
Let's all thank Luis again.

